Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper also discusses information theory and coordination, which are related to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions field trial results and theoretical studies, which are related to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.COM (Computers and Society).
